00:01:11.010 --> 00:01:17.030
But a perfect mirror reflects all colors equally.
So, in a way, you could say that a mirror

00:01:17.030 --> 00:01:23.170
is white, except a mirror doesn't reflect
colors in the same way that pigment does.

00:01:23.170 --> 00:01:30.440
A mirror reflects incoming light in a single
outgoing direction - specular reflection, not

00:01:30.440 --> 00:01:35.250
diffuse. This kind of reflection creates an
image of the very thing in front of the mirror.

00:01:35.480 --> 00:01:40.820
